Contains the following (in no particular order):

	Migrated to Android Studio.
	Theme changes.

	Added Select all action.
    Implemented persistent scroll positions for all paths. (retained until app exits)
	Removed dark theme.
	Removed third party actions from CAB.
	Removed dependency on OI distribution.

(split)OI File Manager: Fix "Send" bug (patch by Alex): The string /mimetype/ was removed from URIs starting with version 1.1.5, but the intent created by the send menu item still sends URIs including /mimetype/. This patch fixes it to be consistent with the content provider.

Update issue 294
A new background thread is created for deleting files and folders.
It supports deleting multi-selected files. 
A toast is shown at the beginning and at the end of the delete action.

TODO:
* add a progress bar (currently only a Toast is shown)

New issue
Summary: OI File Manager: copy and move in thread showing progress bar
Labels: Type-Defect, Priority-Medium, Stack-FileManager
Similar to issue 294, but extend it to also support copy and move commands.

title: (split)OI File Manager: Drop "mimetype" from the provider path. In this way, the…
message:
(split)OI File Manager: Drop "mimetype" from the provider path. In this way, the file name can be obtained using "getPath()" on the URI, as it used to work prior to OI File Manager 1.1.4. This just affects applications that obtain the file path directly from the URI returned. Applications that properly query the provider are not affected by this change.

title: (split)OI File Manager: apply patch by Dominik Pretzsch. The Provider is now…
message:
(split)OI File Manager: apply patch by Dominik Pretzsch. The Provider is now able to handle projections.

I implemented OpenableColumns.DISPLAY_NAME and OpenableColumns.SIZE according 
to Android docs, DATA and MIME_TYPE stay the same. If no projection is passed it'll work with DATA, MIME_TYPE, DISPLAY_NAME and SIZE in that order as a standard projection. DATA and MIME_TYPE stay at their positions, so that 3rd party code using hard-coded indices and passing no projection will stay compatible. 

Fixes issue 324.

title: (split)OI File Manager: Apply patch by Dominik Pretzsch: Copy of file - internationalization.
message:
(split)OI File Manager: Apply patch by Dominik Pretzsch: Copy of file - internationalization.

If a file exists having the same name, it'll split the file's name and extension. 
After that fileName is passed to getString() without extension to build the localized "Copy of"-String, which is then concatenated with correct extension. 

For files without extension or linux style hidden files (e.g '.foo') the file name is not split. 

Fixes issue 307.
